  "notes": "Proto-Mashriqi (Eastern) Arabic — abstract ancestor node for Egyptian, Sudanese, Levantine, Iraqi, and Gulf Arabic. Key shared Eastern features: short vowels generally retained; ج /dʒ/ preserved; ث → /t/, ذ → /d/ in sedentary varieties; ض → /dˤ/ (lateral lost); long vowels maintained.",
